DamageArbiter code

This folder contains the scripts used to reproduce the manuscript experiments:

- `vit_baseline_oof.py`: image-only ViT baseline template. It defaults to
  ViT-B/32, the strongest image-only baseline used in the final DamageArbiter
  comparison. Set `VIT_MODEL_NAME=vit_base_patch16_224` to run ViT-B/16.
- `clip-enhance/`: CLIPScore and CLIP-based multimodal baseline scripts using
  human or LLM-generated descriptions.
- `arbitration/damage_arbiter.py`: disagreement-driven logistic-regression
  arbitrator used for the final DamageArbiter evaluation.
- `LLM-label/`: GPT and Gemini image-description generation scripts.
- `calibration/`: optional confidence-calibration utilities for diagnostics.

Most scripts were written for a Colab-style workflow and contain editable data
paths near the top of each file.
